## Common Mistakes

### Wrong Code
```javascript
function doubleVal(val) {
  let res = val * 2;
}
```
*Why this is incorrect:* Omitting the return statement causes the logic to execute, but the calling script receives None/undefined.

### Correct Code
```javascript
function doubleVal(val) {
  return val * 2;
}
```
*Why this is correct:* Validates statements cleanly.
